                            <comment id="12806527" author="pkamath" created="Fri, 29 Jan 2010 21:59:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch addresses the issue - a couple of data structures in Schema are only used by the front-end query planning code to figure out lineage to handle casts of bytearrays. These data structures don&apos;t need to be serialized to the backend. Hence in the patch they are marked transient which fixes the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
